fy; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University is in agreement with the points made in the response submitted by the Russell Group Equality Forum, of which we are a member.  We endorse that submission and al</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">so that of the Royal Society of Chemistry</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (RSC)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 12.63pt; padding-left:5.37pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Royal Society of Edinburgh’s ‘Tapping all our Talents’ report</span><a name="_ednref1"></a><a href="#_edn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and the League of European Research Universities’ ‘Women, research and universities:  excellence without gender bias’ position paper</span><a name="_ednref2"></a><a href="#_edn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> are v</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">aluable sources of information and recommendations for universities and government.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Demonstrated support at senior management levels is a key success factor.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 12.63pt; padding-left:5.37pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Unconscious bias is an important issue and we would encourage both further research and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">dissemination of research findings in this area.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 11.41pt; padding-left:6.59pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Athena SWAN Charter is a valuable tool for the promotion of the careers of women in STEM and should be funded to enable the benefits to be sustained for the long-term.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Consideration should be given to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">assessing the impact on gender equality of the mechanisms for assessing and funding research.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Scottish Resource Centre for Women in Science, Engineering and Technology is a valuable source of expertise and practical support, and should be funded for t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he long-term.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.81pt; padding-left:7.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Breaks or disruption to women’s work can have a significant impact</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and effective management and support in relation to discontinuity are important.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 10.81pt; padding-left:7.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ole models and mentors </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">have an important role</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for women in STEM careers and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  universities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">should facilitate mentoring.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">The University of Edinburgh</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> document represents the views of The University of Edinburgh. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> one of the largest and most successful universities in the UK with an international reputation as a centre of academic exc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ellence. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the leading resear</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ch university in Scotland and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> amongst the top ten in the United Kingdom. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Based on t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he results of the 2008 Research Assessment Exercise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, the University is home to 37% of Scotland’s 4*</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> “world-leading” research. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">University is committed to developing a positive culture, where all staff and students are able to develop</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to their full potential.  We aim to embed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> equality </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">across all our</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> work and ha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ve</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> integrated equality and diversity into successive strategic plans.  T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he most recent, the Strategic Plan 2012-16, includes three gender-related targets:  to achieve a University Athena SWAN Silver award; to increase the proportion of female academic staff appointed and promoted; and to reduce the gender pay gap. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University has a track record of strategic commitment and success on the promotion of gender equality.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We were</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> among the first to sign the Athena SWAN Charter and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">we </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">obtained a Br</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">onze University award in 2006, which we have</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> successfully renewed twice.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">School of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Chemistry is one of only three</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ‘departments’ in the UK to hold a Gold award</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  Our Schools of Biomedical Sciences and Biological Sciences have S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ilver Athena SWAN awards, and our</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Royal (Dick) School of Veterinary Medicine and the Roslin Insti</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tute have Bronze awards.  All of our remaining sch</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ools </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are committed to working towards achieving Athena SWAN or equivalent awards</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University has participated in programmes run by the UK higher education sector</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’s Equality Challenge Unit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, including th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e Advancing Gender Equality Systemic Change Pilot during 2011-13.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  We also participate in the League of European Research Universities’ Gender Working Group.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of Edinburgh</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> retained the HR Excellence in Research Award from the Eu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ropean Co</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mmission in 2013.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> This award </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">demonstrates </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">our</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> commitment to improving the working conditions and career development for research staff</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and embedding the principles of the Concordat to Support the Career Development of Researchers</span><a name="_ednref3"></a><a href="#_edn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our submission </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">inquiry on women in STEM careers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is made in the spirit of actively promoting equality, diversity and inclusion.  We welcome the opportun</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ity to comment on this topic.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Relevant data</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University publishes an annual Equality and Diversity Monitoring and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Rese</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">arch Committee (EDMARC) report.  The last three reports can be found at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">http://www.ed.ac.uk/schools-departments/equality-diversity/monitoring-statisti</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cs/edmarc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> These reports consistently show a reduction in the proportion of women in academic roles at each stage of the career ladder.  This pattern of grade by grade ‘drop off’ is broadly similar in all acad</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mic areas.  However, the proportion of femal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e staff is considerably lower at the outset in most STEM subjects. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Why do numbers of women in STEM academic careers decline further up the career ladder?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University considers that the responses submitted by the Russell Group Equality Forum and the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> RSC address the key reasons for the declining numbers of women further up the STEM academic career ladder.  However, we would </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">like to highlight the following points.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We have come to be increasingly influenced by the research findings that concern </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">unconscious bias against women in recruitment and selection</span><a name="_ednref4"></a><a href="#_edn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and other processes</span><a name="_ednref5"></a><a href="#_edn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  We recognise the importance of considering research of this kind and are seeking to disseminate the findings as widely as possible within our own institution with a view to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> raising awareness and understanding of the impact of unconscious bias on women’s careers.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> would highlight research in relation to gender in the Engineering profession, regarding the roles of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">self-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">confidence</span><a name="_ednref6"></a><a href="#_edn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and of both structural barriers and gender </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">dynamics</span><a name="_ednref7"></a><a href="#_edn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">It is clear in information gathered from women in science over a number of years </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that one of the main difficulties for women is managing discontinuity in their work.  Breaks or disruption, whether due to maternity leave or other reasons, are s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">een as having potentially significant negative impacts on women’s careers if they are not managed and supported well.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Finally, in relation to this question, we want to make special mention of the Royal Society of Edinburgh</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’s (RSE) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">April 2012 report, ‘Ta</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">pping all our Talents:  Women in science, technology, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">engineering and mathematics:  a strategy for Scotland’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  We view this as a tremendous resumé of the challenges and potential for women in STEM in Scotland – across all sectors – and believe it makes a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">valuable contribution to discussion of this issue world-wide.  This report has been extremely beneficial in developing understanding across institutions and is important for focusing attention on the current position and the potential that we want to retai</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">When women leave academia, what careers do they transition into? What are the consequences of scientifically trained women applying their skills in different employment sectors?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The data in this area is limited.  However, it is clear from the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">data in the RSE’s Tapping all our Talents repor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t¹</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that in Scotland the majority of female STEM graduates are in non-STEM occupations.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">What should universities and the higher education sector do to retain woman graduates and PhD students in academic caree</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">rs? Are there examples of good practice?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University considers that the responses submitted by the Russell Group Equality Forum and the RSC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">highlight potential action for universities and the sector in this respect.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> However, we would </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">also</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> like to highlight the following points.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Universities should ensure that there is demonstrated </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">support at senior management levels </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">– as this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">seems to be a key success factor. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In view of the potential impact of discontin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uity for academic careers (see 11</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">above), universities and the higher education sector should provide support for women in returning to work following any break, whether due to maternity leave or other reasons</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, to prevent disruption to their work and careers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">All encouragement and any </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">guidance that can contribute to creating the best pos</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sible practices in this area are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">most helpful.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">At the University, we have found the Athena SWAN award process to be a very helpful tool in the institution – particularly for STEM subjects, but increas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ingly also more widely.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">From our discussions with women in STEM, we would especially wish to emphasise the importance that they attribute to role models and the availability of mentoring to support them in their career development.  Universities and the h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">igher education </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sector </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">have an important role to play in encouraging and facilitating mentoring.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Another aspect that is routinely raised is childcare provision and its availability and flexibility.  We have recently reviewed our childcare provision on t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he strength of the express need for improved access to childcare close to work for women in science.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Universities should also examine their structures and practices for reward and recognition with particular attention to the impact on women in STEM.  In a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ddition to our annual equality monitoring reports, we have introduced biennial equal pay audits, with</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> additional</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> annual analysis of pay at professorial level, with a view to identifying and addressing areas of concern.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Finally, on this point, we should like to highlight </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and endorse </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> League of European Research Universities’ (LERU’s) July 2012 position paper ‘Women, research and universities:  excellence without gender bias’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">²</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, to which the University of Edinburgh contr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ibuted through LERU’s Gender Working Group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  LERU includes five UK Higher Education Institutions:  the Universities of Cambridge, Edinburgh and Oxford, Imperial College London and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">University College London.  That</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> paper sets out a number of priorities for a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ction by universities, by funders of research and by governments.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">What role should the Government have in encouraging the retention of women in academic STEM careers?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University considers that the responses submitted by the Russell Group Equality Forum and the RSC highlight a number of important roles for the Government.  However, we would </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">like to highlight the following points.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University has</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> collected </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eq</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uality data for some time, producing substantial monitoring reports in relation to both staff and students annually.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rom our experience of developing data collection and data analysis, we are persuaded of the importance of securing more comp</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rehensive dat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a for both academia and industry, which enables cross-institutional and international comparisons and provides evidence to inform policy.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We would note the importance of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gathering and analysing data that looks beyond gender alone, and considers the inters</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ection between gender and other protected characteristics, such as age or race. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We consider the Athena SWAN scheme to be an excellent catalyst for culture change in relation to the employment of women in STEM in higher education.  It is therefore importa</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nt that funding for the Athena SWAN Charter is put in place at the right level for the long-term, to enable the benefits to be sustained.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We would suggest that full equality impact assessment is undertaken on the assessment and funding of research through</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Research Councils, and through </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Research Excellence Framework</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> controlled by</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">via</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the Higher Educat</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ion Funding Council for England</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Universities and research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> funding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">councils should together develop better, more effective ways of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">managing maternity/</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">parental leave</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and supporting women through periods of discontinuity in their work</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We should like to highlight again LERU’s position paper ‘Women, research and universitie</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s:  excellence without gender bias’², which sets out a number of priorities for action by funders of research and by governments. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Finally, on this point, w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e very much welcome the continued funding by the Scottish Government of the Scottish Resource Centr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for Women in Science, Engineering and Technology, which provides expertise and practical support</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, including training and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">development for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">individual women in STEM careers and for managers/institutions wishing to further the careers of women in STEM.  The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">SRC also</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> facilitates good practice and collaboration, both between Higher Education</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Institutions and with industry</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as an institution, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">have both contributed to and benefited from this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Centre.  It is important that this Centre should continue to be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">funded on a long-term basis, to enable it to develop as the recognised authority in this field, building its research, expertise, guidance and practical support services and developing best practice. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Conclusion</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Unive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rsity of Edinburgh welcomes the S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cience and Technology Committee’s inquiry into Women in STEM careers and welcomes this opportunity to comment.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">References</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_edn1"></a><a href="#_ednref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Royal Society 